title: 724 Columbus Avenue - West 95th Street

text:
March 29, 1969

West 95th St. N. side, looking N.E. toward Columbus Ave.

Note: 6 identical buildings:
Nos. 121-119-117-115-113-111

No. 115 in 1897 was occupied by Dr. P.F. O'Hanlon, father of "Virginia" of the famous "Santa Claus" editional [sic]. N.Y. SUN Sept 21, 1897

No. 121 - Occupied in later years by Dr. O'Hanlon

No. 113 - Occupied until 1918 by Dr. Floyd Milford Crandall, Sec. of N.Y. County Medical Soc., Author of "How to Keep Well" (Doubleday - Page & Co. N.Y. 1903)

No. 111 - only house still occupied 1969 by Mrs. John Devlin

Above buildings are in West Side Urban Renewal Program
